Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.16,0:16:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,external peace,\N>> peaceful situation, surroundings.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.39,0:16:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,um\Nyou can be at peace with a emotional
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.75,0:16:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,state that is not peaceful.\NSo by that meaning of peace we mean
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.51,0:16:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,total acceptance.\NI can totally accept that at a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.39,0:16:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,time I be may be stricken with guilt or\Nat a second certain time I might be
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.92,0:16:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,stricken with anger or anger you know\Nthat it might be a non
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.68,0:16:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,during the war uh\Nyou know
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.72,0:16:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at on the one hand at peace all\Nthe time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.44,0:16:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,uh I was on a mind sweeper you can get\Nblown up any instant
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.51,0:16:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So there I am living with we live I\Nlearned to live at peace with the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.07,0:16:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,possibility of instant death.\NInstant death and and a couple times it
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.63,0:17:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,almost happened. The ship came\Nand the horn sticking out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.12,0:17:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,mine, you know, actually began to bump\Nthe edge of the ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.19,0:17:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So admittedly, I was prepared to go to\NGod right then. that any moment you're
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.00,0:17:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,going to explode into a million pieces.\NSo you have to be at peace
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.76,0:17:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,with the possibility of imminent death\Nat any second.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.31,0:17:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And and the ship would would just touch,\Nyou know, there's this mine and it's got
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.88,0:17:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,these horns sticking out and the wave\Nwould come like this and the ship would
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,come like this and it would just touch\Nthe horn, touch the edge of the horn of
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.08,0:17:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,this mine.\NAnd curiously enough, I was at inner
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.44,0:17:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,peace that any instant\NI may suddenly go to thee, oh Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.28,0:17:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Amen.\NAnd uh
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.52,0:18:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,taking taking the ship through a\Ntyphoon, you know, at any second we the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.36,0:18:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,inclinometer hit actually 90° which is\Nhorizontal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.55,0:18:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm standing on the wall, standing\Non the bulkhead, steering the ship, and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.55,0:18:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,at any moment we may explode from\Nhitting this mo mine or drown from the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.96,0:18:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,typhoon going on. And so, I'm living\Nwith the possibility of instant death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.48,0:18:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And yet, I was completely at peace with\Nit. Completely surrendered. If you
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.36,0:18:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,explode, you explode.\N>> If you drown, you drowned. If the ship
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,goes over, the ship goes over.\N>> Do you remember when we were traveling
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.52,0:18:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and we were going back to New York and\Num the plane at the time the it never
