Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.36,0:18:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,a forced landing and there were uh fire\Ntrucks lining the the runway and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.96,0:19:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,everything and the Yeah. Do you remember\Nthat? Anyway, there it was one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.55,0:19:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,times and I can remember when the pilot\Nwhen the pilot came on and says we're
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.64,0:19:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,going to have to land in Albuquerque and\Nwe and we just looked at each other
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.52,0:19:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> your seat belts.\N>> Yeah. And we just looked at each other
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.32,0:19:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and we had the most it was just like\Nokay if we go we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.55,0:19:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's right. We're starting now's our\Ntime to go. We're going to die. If
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.32,0:19:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to die now you die,\N>> right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.48,0:19:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So you accept the imminence and\Npossibility. In fact, even the
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.00,0:19:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,likelihood of sudden death. And yet,\Nyou're completely at peace about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.00,0:19:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And we looked over at each other and we\Ngrabbed each other's hands and you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.24,0:19:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the plane came down.\N>> That's right. If we crash, we crash. And
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.52,0:19:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if we don't don't, we don't.\N>> So, there was peace, right? Oh, I see
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.00,0:19:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,what the point you're making.\NPeace is possible right in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.28,0:19:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,extreme danger.\N>> Exactly. I mean, we were both we were
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.79,0:20:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,exposed to the imminence of likelihood\Nin fact of sudden death at any instant
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.03,0:20:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and yet we were both at peace with it.\NWe looked at each other and said, "Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.60,0:20:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> okay,\N>> if we're going now, we're going now."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.64,0:20:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> And that was it.\N>> And there was no problem. So what's the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.96,0:20:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,problem?\N>> They both die, we die now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.67,0:20:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we were dying together.\NSo that made it even more more, you
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.60,0:20:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,know, easy.\NBut uh during the war where I didn't
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.76,0:20:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have a part partner, I accepted the fact\Nthat we could blow up at any instant
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.44,0:20:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and I felt a piece about it.\NWe came very close to close to exploding
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.67,0:20:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and you was a piece about it. And I I\Nwas at the wheel during the great
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.40,0:20:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Okanawa typhoon which is a very famous\Ntyphoon went on for three days and 90
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.44,0:20:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,ships 90 ships went down in the typhoon\Nand I was at the wheel for three days
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.28,0:21:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh\Nand I would sleep for like 10 10 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.44,0:21:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and then go back to the wheel for an\Nhour or two because I wasn't seasick.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.36,0:21:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody was seasick and I uh I was\Nnever seasick.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.00,0:21:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah, you said it was. And uh so I just\Nkept going.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.67,0:21:22.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As I say, the ship was sideways. I was\Nstanding on the bulkhead at 90 degrees.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.12,0:21:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh so you can be in the middle of\Nabsolute extreme danger and be at peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.32,0:21:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was at totally at inner peace\Nabout it. If you blow up, you blow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.79,0:21:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you do, you don't. And if you\Ndon't, you don't. So
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.60,0:21:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,complete and total acceptance of the\Ntotality of the experience
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.28,0:21:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> sudden death was not only possible it\Nwas very likely
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.28,0:21:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> but you know in that in that uh in that\Nsetting that I'm talking about on the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.55,0:21:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,plane and we were sitting there I mean\N>> you think about everyone going oh no oh
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.12,0:22:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,no in the plane and everybody was dead\Nsilence it was just like eerie
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.24,0:22:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think everybody was praying too.\N>> Yes, they had to. But everyone was It
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.64,0:22:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,was just dead silence.\N>> Yeah. Yeah. Because they came around
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.88,0:22:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,said, "Prepare for a crash landing,\Ndidn't they?"
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.36,0:22:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yes. And they told us that we'd have to\NWe had to bend over and put our head
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.03,0:22:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,between our legs.\N>> Yes. At the buck of your seat belt.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.55,0:22:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> You had to put your pillow on your lap,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.64,0:22:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right?\N>> And put your head on your pillow,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.64,0:22:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> right?\N>> And prepare for prepared to die. Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.03,0:22:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, we looked at each other and held\Neach other. And we thought if we go and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.24,0:22:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,we go and if we don't we don't.\N>> So, and uh we didn't. Did we?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.32,0:22:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No.\N>> I guess we did.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.44,0:22:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I guess we not. We're not. We're still\Nhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.96,0:22:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But we were prepared.\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.36,0:22:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> But that was that's a very nice example.\NAnd the plane tells you we're prepared
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.79,0:22:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for a crash landing. Put your head on\Nyour pillow.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.40,0:23:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh strangely enough,\Nprofound state of peace comes to you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.60,0:23:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when you totally accept it. If you\Nresist it, you become frightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.36,0:23:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> But when you totally accept the fear, it
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.28,0:23:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,disappears it. That's a very good\Nexample. Yeah. The example between fear
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.03,0:23:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and anxiety and life and death\N>> and inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.55,0:23:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. And inner peace. Yeah.\NWe looked at each other and said, "If we
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.64,0:23:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,leave now, we're leaving now." So\NIf you live, you live. And if you die,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.32,0:23:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you die. That's it.\NTotal acceptance of the possibility of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.20,0:23:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the realities of existence brings about\Nan inner peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.40,0:23:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So even though there could be even\Nthough there is chaos around you, um
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.52,0:23:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,there's still this inner peace that\Nprevails.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.72,0:23:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's interesting. That's true. Just\Nlike you in the ship, you know, this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.48,0:23:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,horn was going to bump the ship and you\Nwere gonna it was going to explode this
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.36,0:24:02.15,Default,,0,0,0,,mine right next to the ship and you grab\Nthe whatever gaffle or whatever it was
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.15,0:24:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and say, "Okay, let's push it away.\NYou pushed it away."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.12,0:24:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's I thought you Well, if we blow\Nup, we blow up and if we don't, we
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.79,0:24:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't.\N>> Yeah. Absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.48,0:24:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, I guess the fastest road to peace is\Ntotal acceptance
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.40,0:24:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of the of the reality of how you're\Nexperienc how however you're
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.03,0:24:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing reality at that moment.\NThe total acceptance of it brings peace
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.91,0:24:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because every time we were near a plane\Ncrash, they would say, "Put your head on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.15,0:24:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,your pillow.\NUm, you know, do this, that, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.48,0:24:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,other." And we felt at peace. I wasn't\Nnervous. Were you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.32,0:24:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> No. Neither one of us. I looked at you\Nand thought, well, if we go, we go, and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.64,0:24:50.79,Default,,0,0,0,,if we don't, we don't.\N>> Also, also though, I mean, we were we
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.79,0:24:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,were doing spiritual work, we were uh\Nspeaking, you know, and um it was like,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.20,0:25:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,okay, if if this is what God has for us,\Nit was acceptance, too,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.52,0:25:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> you know,\N>> but it doesn't necessarily have to be
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.72,0:25:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,couched in spiritual terms. No,\N>> because during the war, I mean, you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.76,0:25:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,know, when when it almost got exploded\Noff of mine, I I think I was an atheist
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.76,0:25:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time.\N>> I don't remember if I can anybody can we
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.20,0:25:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,use the arm?\N>> No, you weren't an atheist at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.44,0:25:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,of the war. It was after that, I think.\N>> I said, can we use the arm or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.20,0:25:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,During the six at the time, I believed\Nin God.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.32,0:25:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, I did believe in God. Oh,\N>> it was later.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.20,0:25:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh,\N>> I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.79,0:25:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm. But I'm just saying that um inner\Npeace is something that's there. You
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.84,0:25:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,just have to\N>> discover that it's already present.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.72,0:25:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um at least that's my understanding.\N>> So you don't discover until you need it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.12,0:25:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you finally\N>> experience that it's always been there.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.64,0:25:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Right.\N>> Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.40,0:26:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Because it seems like it's there in\Ntimes of crisis when you really need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.84,0:26:07.96,Default,,0,0,0,,That inner peace and knowing is always\Nthere.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.00,0:26:12.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right. And the other\Npassengers were the same. They said,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.24,0:26:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,"Put your head on your pillow. Prepare\Nfor a crash landing."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.12,0:26:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I think they said, "Put a your head on\Nyour lap." There wasn't any
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.08,0:26:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, whatever it was, uh there wasn't\Nany widespread panic at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.72,0:26:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> In fact, peace prevailed in the whole\Ncabin of that that airplane.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.96,0:26:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> Nobody started to scream, "Help! Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:30.64,0:26:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Help!" There was no hysteria, no\Nscreaming.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.88,0:26:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There was absolute peace and quiet.\NEverybody put their head on their pillow
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.55,0:26:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and prepared to die.\NIt was a very profound moment. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.72,0:26:48.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.72,0:26:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um\Ndo you think that um you can obtain an
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.60,0:26:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,inner peace by fulfilling a a goal or a\Num task?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.91,0:27:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is that inner peace or is that something\Nelse? I no I think that's inner peace
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.44,0:27:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,where you set a goal for yourself and\Nthen fulfill that goal
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.00,0:27:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,because it leaves nothing uh undone.\N>> Inner peace is I have a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.40,0:27:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,expectation in myself that as we sit\Nhere you and I I will spontaneously be
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.55,0:27:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,honest to the my greatest capacity.\NI may not be the most fluent. I I've
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.12,0:27:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,probably been more fluent at other\Ntimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.32,0:27:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but I um my inner expectation is that I\Nwill feel completely secure, at ease,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.08,0:27:44.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and at one with you as we answer these\Nquestions. And that I know I will be
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.96,0:27:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,doing the best that I possibly can do\Nunder the circumstance.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.48,0:27:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mh.\N>> And that if I was capable of being more
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.60,0:27:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,uh eloquent or fluent, I would be. So I\Nhow however whatever the potentiality I
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.64,0:28:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,have of being at this moment is being\Nfulfilled at this very moment. So I am
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.72,0:28:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,already becoming and have become the\Ncomplete fulfillment of my highest
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.64,0:28:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,expectations of myself that I will be\Nfluent and eloquent when I ask to to be
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.72,0:28:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,so or maybe useful to others\Nwhen making something useful with others
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.88,0:28:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,always adds value to me. you know, I do\Na better job
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.32,0:28:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,>> I do a better job of something\N>> if I know it's going to serve some other
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.39,0:28:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,purpose, you know.\N>> So,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.08,0:28:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is there a certain amount of inner peace\Nwhen you donate your life to God?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.44,0:28:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh, I think to any\N>> I think it brings a profound sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.88,0:28:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,peace. Yes.\Nuh what I do now I ask God to help me do
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.48,0:28:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it to the best of my ability\Nthat I may thereby be serving God.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.84,0:29:04.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh\Nmy obligation to divinity is to be the
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.96,0:29:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,fulfillment of\Nmy own potentiality to the best of my
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.76,0:29:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,capacity.\N>> Mhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.60,0:29:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,>> To be as fluent as I can be\Nso that other other people's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.96,0:29:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,understanding of it will be uh\Naided and embedded by our discussing. So
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.00,0:29:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,our dis are discussing what this means\Nto us
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.48,0:29:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,brings the same question up in others.\NWhat does my existence mean to me? What
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.96,0:29:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,does my existence mean to my wife? What\Ndoes my existence mean to my family
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.24,0:29:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and to mankind? Am I being all that I\Ncan be for the sake of mankind?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.88,0:29:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of times I think of my own\Nexistence as serving
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.44,0:29:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,a multitude of purposes simultaneously.\NMhm.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.52,0:30:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Um when in the eastern religions we have\Nmeditative states and a lot of people
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.55,0:30:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,refer to that meditative state as their\Ninner peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.55,0:30:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Oh yes\N>> state.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.76,0:30:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah. So um would you say that\Nmeditation is a form of inner peace or
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.44,0:30:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,is it just the\Nvessel that inner peace is brought forth
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.79,0:30:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to recognize? Well, I think it's\Nboth s is both simultaneously.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.91,0:30:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,U\Ninner peace is a is a profound state.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.03,0:30:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> Uh
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.36,0:30:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,true inner peace cannot be uh disturbed\Nby disturbance. As paradoxical as that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.84,0:30:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,may sound,\N>> uh, right now I feel I'm fulfilling what
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.15,0:30:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm supposed to be doing with you to the\Nbest of my ability
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.52,0:31:00.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing deserves that peace because\NI know what that intention is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.24,0:31:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Now, if I fail to achieve that\Nintention, I'm still going to stay at
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.79,0:31:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,peace because I did the best I could at\Nthe time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.79,0:31:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If I could have done better, I would\Nhave. So I'm being as eloquent as I can
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.72,0:31:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,be at this moment under these\Ncircumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.96,0:31:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That doesn't mean that hypothetically I\Ncouldn't be more eloquent at other
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.48,0:31:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,moments\Nuh or other other circumstances.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:26.39,0:31:31.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So our overall intention\NI think tends to dominate the quality of
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.84,0:31:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience.\NUm, my overall intention is to express
Dialogue: 0,0:31:38.08,0:31:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,love for God, for you, for my fellow\Nhuman being, for the people here in the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.84,0:31:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,room all simultaneously.\N>> I love the photographer. I love the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.91,0:31:56.08,Default,,0,0,0,,witnesses. I love the people who help\Nmove the furniture.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.08,0:32:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I I love the all that is at this moment\Nequally, you might say.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.84,0:32:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't love this wall more than I do\Nthis window. There's like a totality
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.72,0:32:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,of um the love of that which exists.\NThe love of all that exists. So that to
Dialogue: 0,0:32:20.55,0:32:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,me divinity is all that exists.\NHow however you may see it or experience
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.20,0:32:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,it is something else. again.\NMhm. Not but that does not influence the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.03,0:32:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,absolute reality of it.\NSo you think I worry too much about the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.12,0:32:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,doggy. So I say well worrying too much\Nabout the doggy is the fulfillment of my
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.12,0:32:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,perfection.\NThe kind of person who worries too much
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.91,0:32:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,about the doggy.\NThat's perfectly who I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.03,0:32:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I worry about the kitties too and the\Nbeauty.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.51,0:33:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> And I worry about you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.67,0:33:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,>> and I worry about our friends\N>> and I worry about everybody sitting in
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.27,0:33:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,this room right this moment that each\None is
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.51,0:33:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,um being fulfilled in their expectations\Nand however
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.24,0:33:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,they might be benefited or uh by what we\Nsay. So would you say that the state
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.51,0:33:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that you feel when you are in a when\Nyou're meditating that state that you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.00,0:33:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,feel when you're meditating you know\Nit's very difficult to quiet the mind
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.84,0:33:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but once you have that you have this\Nkind of peacefulness that comes over you
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.44,0:33:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> oh yeah that's a profound state of\N>> that's a profound state all right so
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.20,0:33:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,this profound state of consciousness is\Nalways there it's just we have to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.84,0:33:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,recognize it within our own aura or\Nwithin our own being
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.76,0:33:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> yes to have it dominate in other words\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.44,0:33:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Right.\N>> Uhhuh.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.03,0:33:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You know, well, a lot of people want to\Nbe in that state all the time. And I
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.91,0:34:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,think it's impossible to be in a\Ncomplete state of inner peace. I mean,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.03,0:34:07.27,Default,,0,0,0,,there's just it's unless you are a monk\Nor
